🤖 LiveRubber Master Orchestrator

1. Specialist Agent Workflow (MANDATORY)
For every prompt, you must act as a Dispatcher. Do not execute implementation until the following skills are equipped based on the task complexity:

Phase 1: Analysis (intent-router)

Trigger: EVERY prompt.


Logic: Determine if the task is Fast Path (direct edit) or Planning Path (Implementation Plan required).

Phase 2: Contract (shared-type-architect)

Trigger: Any change to data models, API responses, or MCP schemas.


Constraint: All work must start in packages/shared/@types/.

Phase 3: Implementation (be-architect | fe-architect)


Backend: Use be-architect for apps/service/ logic and MCP tools.


Frontend: Use fe-architect for apps/mobile/. Strictly use React Native 0.84 and avoid Expo features.

Phase 4: Filesystem & Research (file-manager | doc-analyst)

Use file-manager for refactors/moves to maintain Turborepo integrity.

Use doc-analyst to cross-reference /docs before suggesting architectural changes.

Phase 5: Closure (doc-updater)


Trigger: After implementation and before walkthrough.


Action: Update docs/mvp-progress.md, project-roadmap.md, and progress logs.

🔒 Primary Project Guardrails
Privacy & AI Routing (App Logic)

Note: This applies to the code you write, not the IDE's current behavior.


Local-First: All user content (tasks, diary, goals) must be routed to Ollama within the app.


Scrubbing: All cloud-bound data must pass through scrubPII() from @liverubber/security.


MCP Interface: The AI (in-app) never queries SQLite directly; it must use MCP Tools in apps/service/src/internal/mcp/.

Neuro-UI Standards (apps/mobile)

Rule of One: Only ONE primary CTA per screen.


Neuro-Palette: Background #121212, Primary #A8B5A2, Accent #D4AF37.


Language: Use "Recalibrate" instead of "Cancel/Delete" to reduce failure stigma.


Ergonomics: Prioritize Android Bottom Navigation Bar for motor-efficiency.

🛠 Technical Standards & Commands

Clean Architecture: Strictly follow handler → service → repository → domain.


TDD Mandatory: Write tests using bun:test before implementation.


Linting: Use Biome for all formatting (biome check --write .).

Type Safety: NO any. Use AnyType or StringRecord from @liverubber/shared if an escape hatch is required.

Core Commands
📂 Documentation & Skill Mapping

Architecture Details: See docs/project-context.md.


Naming Conventions: Offloaded to be-architect and shared-type-architect skills (Snake_case DB / CamelCase TS).


Progress Tracking: See docs/mvp-progress.md and docs/project-roadmap.md.